# Clerk — authentication + billing (Clerk Billing; Stripe is the processor).
# Get this from the Clerk Dashboard → API Keys. The VITE_ prefix is required
# so Vite exposes it to the browser. The publishable key is safe to ship;
# only the Secret Key must never touch the frontend (this app doesn't use it).
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxx

# ── Setup checklist (Clerk Dashboard) ───────────────────────────────────────
#  1. Create an application → copy the Publishable Key above into .env.
#  2. Billing → Settings → enable Billing.
#  3. For DEVELOPMENT you can use Clerk's built-in development payment gateway
#     (a shared test Stripe account) — no Stripe account needed to test checkout.
#     For PRODUCTION, connect your own live Stripe account here.
#  4. Billing → Subscription plans → "Plans for Users" tab → Add Plan.
#     Give it the slug "pro" (or change PLAN_SLUG in src/game/billing.js) and
#     set its price.
#
# Clerk then manages users and their subscriptions in its dashboard. No Stripe
# secret key is needed in this app — Clerk talks to Stripe for you.
#
# ⚠️  Heads-up about a Stripe product you may have already created:
#   • Clerk Billing does NOT import or reuse existing Stripe products/prices.
#     Plans are defined in Clerk (step 4); Stripe only processes the payment.
#     Re-create your price as a Clerk plan — your standalone Stripe product is
#     ignored.
#   • To connect your own Stripe account it must not already be on another
#     platform — disconnect any existing Stripe Connect platform first.
#   • A development-instance Stripe connection is sandbox-only and cannot be
#     used for production; connect a live account on your production instance.
